    region: "Courtyard",
    desc: "Dead trees stand like blackened bones against the grey sky. A cracked sundial shows a time that doesn't match the sun's position - off by exactly six hours, as if measuring time in a different place. The ground bears scorch marks in patches, and nothing grows in those marks.",
