      "scorch marks": "The scorch marks form a pattern when viewed from above. You can't see it from ground level, but you sense geometry in the destruction - and nothing grows in the marks, though moss crowds their edges like an audience.",
      trees: "Blackened bark flakes at a touch. Beneath it the wood is not burnt but hollowed - each trunk a dry pipe standing in the earth. Wind moving across them should make sound. You wait. It declines to.",
