    desc: "Shelves line every wall, floor to ceiling. Most hold dust and mouse skeletons, but some containers are sealed with wax and still intact - among them a loaf gone hard as ship's biscuit and a stoppered red vial someone cached and never came back for. The air is cold here - unnaturally cold, your breath misting before you. In the corner, a trapdoor is nailed shut from this side. Whatever is below, someone wanted it to stay there.",
